quotas.name: West Bengal Govt Quota
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : West Bengal Govt Quota**

Should be a domicile of WB. Any one of the below

1. Proforma a1. Residing in WB continuously at least last 10 years as on 31st Dec 2023 (for 2024). Also should be X and XII passed from West Bengal. To be signed by Govt authorities in list - DM and a few,SP and a few Commissioner/AC and so on....(OR)   
2. Proforma a2. Residing in WB continuously at least last 10 years as on 31st Dec 2023 (for 2024). Also passed XII from West Bengal in 2024 (For 2024). To be signed by Head Master/Principal/Director/ Head of the Institution where the candidate has studied XII (OR)    
3. Proforma b) If not in above, if parent/s are permanent resident/s of West Bengal having their permanent home address within West Bengal and living continuously for at least last 10 years in West Bengal as on 31st Dec 2023 (For 2024). To be signed by Govt authorities in list - DM and a few,SP and a few Commissioner/AC and so on.... In this case (3rd criteria) any two of Voter ID or Aadhaar Card or Passport showing residential address of WB is to be produced.         
**Should not have applied for NRI Quota in WB state counselling"**

quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : West Bengal Management Quota**

All India Basis (Should not have applied for NRI Quota in WB state counselling)

quotas.name: West Bengal NRI Quota
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : West Bengal NRI Quota**

NRI/OCI Candidates All India Basis as per SC order (will not be eligible for Govt or Management seats)

**Eligibility for the Quota : West Bengal Govt Quota**

Should be a domicile of WB. Any one of the below

1. Proforma a1. Residing in WB continuously at least last 10 years as on 31st Dec 2023 (for 2024). Also should be X and XII passed from West Bengal. To be signed by Govt authorities in list - DM and a few,SP and a few Commissioner/AC and so on....(OR)   
2. Proforma a2. Residing in WB continuously at least last 10 years as on 31st Dec 2023 (for 2024). Also passed XII from West Bengal in 2024 (For 2024). To be signed by Head Master/Principal/Director/ Head of the Institution where the candidate has studied XII (OR)    
3. Proforma b) If not in above, if parent/s are permanent resident/s of West Bengal having their permanent home address within West Bengal and living continuously for at least last 10 years in West Bengal as on 31st Dec 2023 (For 2024). To be signed by Govt authorities in list - DM and a few,SP and a few Commissioner/AC and so on.... In this case (3rd criteria) any two of Voter ID or Aadhaar Card or Passport showing residential address of WB is to be produced.         
**Should not have applied for NRI Quota in WB state counselling"**
